In this film Barbie and her friends are gymnasts, and they become spies after a real spy recognizes their talents. With their high tech tools, toys and equipment, they are off to save the day from gem stealing criminals. This is a very cute film.

Barbie films feature some intelligent friends and ones that don't do as well, but they all have a lesson to them. I enjoy watching with my granddaughter, a good cuddling and bonding time.

Charlie's Angels meets Barbie! It's a very fun, colorful movie that really does show the true meaning of teamwork and girl power. "Spy Squad" is familiar if you're a fan of the old-school spy shows, and if you've seen movies like "Ultraviolet" with use of "dimension compressing technology", and even Star Wars with the G.L.I.S., a glowing, expandable launching stick that could be summoned back to Barbie, much like the light saber of the Star Wars saga. You'll find easter eggs reminiscent of past Barbie films hidden throughout the movie. I think the film is a great way to encourage girls that they can use their brains and their bodies for much more than just beauty and vanity.

I'm been watching Barbie ever since I was a little girl. (I'm 18 now) The classic Barbie movies will always be my favorites and have the most sentimental value but I still enjoy watching the new ones when I can. This one is by far my favorite since the Fairytopia ones and thoses go way back! The new ones are good, but they attempt to be more modern and simple which is unnecessary for Barbie. As a young girl, I was able to follow along the storyline of a princess and a pauper wishing for freedom from their unfortunatd duties to a family of 12 dancing sisters who go on a magical journey of a lifetime. My point is, children are smarter then we may think and don't need simple corny writing. Barbie did a great job with this movie by having a storyline simple enough for kids but elaborate and detailed enough for adults to enjoy as well. That is why I still watch the movies! They caught my attention then and they still have it now! What I liked most about this movie, is that there are multiple nods to others Barbie movies as well as detail. The dress up scene had a lot of dresses that I recognized from the other newer Barbie movies which gave the movie sentiment. Also, I loved how the love interest was between the inventor (Lazlo) and Barbie' s friend (Teresa). It's nice to see that not every guy in a Barbie movie falls for Barbie. This gave Barbie and her friends a lot of personality. Lastly, I love the spy animation with the action and gadgets. I miss the old Barbie look, but I could learn to love this new animation. Girls of any age could come to love this movie. It has great morals of teamwork, see it and be it, and following your dreams.  I'm hoping for a Spy Squad 2!

If these girls are supposed to be spies they'd know how to "blend" in and be prepared to do their job.  And they'd be intelligent.
